"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is incorrectly using both `ax.set_xticks()` and `ax.xaxis.set_major_locator()` to set the x-axis ticks. `ax.set_xticks()` is used to set the tick locations manually, while `ax.xaxis.set_major_locator()` is used to set the tick locations automatically based on a locator. Using both can cause conflicts and lead to unexpected results.\",\n  \"patch\": \"17,18c17\\n< ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n< ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\\n---\\n> # Removed manual tick setting to avoid conflict with MonthLocator\\n\"\n}"